Package: qshapr
Type: Package
Title: Feature-Specific R-Squared Values for Tree Ensembles
Version: 1.0
Date: 2025-02-18
Authors@R: c(
    person("Zhongli", "Jiang", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "zhongli.jiang@example.com"),
    person("Min", "Zhang", role = "aut"),
    person("Dabao", "Zhang", role = "aut"))
Description: Computes feature-specific R-squared values using Shapley decomposition 
    of the total R-squared for tree ensembles in polynomial time. Supports XGBoost 
    and LightGBM models with parallel processing capabilities. Based on the method 
    described in Jiang, Zhang, and Zhang (2024) "Fast Calculation of Feature 
    Contributions in Boosting Trees".
License: GPL (>= 2)
URL: https://github.com/catstats/Q-SHAP_R
BugReports: https://github.com/catstats/Q-SHAP_R/issues
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.14), xgboost (>= 3.1.3.1), parallel, lightgbm,
        data.table, viridisLite, scales, ggplot2, jsonlite, methods,
        progress
Suggests: shiny
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppEigen
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Encoding: UTF-8
